    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="856"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your No. 33 received.</p>
                <p>It was held by us in Porto Rico that the armament of forts, fortifications, and
                    fixed batteries were to be included in the surrender and taken over into the
                    possession of the United States. The Spanish army was to take with it small arms
                    and accouterments, batteries and field artillery of 9 centimeters caliber,
                    supply and baggage wagons, ambulances, and other impedimenta.</p>
                <p>The President thinks it undesirable to include in treaty any preferential
                    privileges to Spain in Cuba or Puerto Rico; and if such privileges tendered by
                    you in Philippines are accepted, care should be taken to avoid possible
                    embarrassments to legislation by Congress or demands by other governments under
                    favored-nation clause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
